{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"085da021-1775-4d99-a478-5f48ff042d44","content":"The directory is empty — there are no existing files. Since you described the page conceptually, here's how to convert it and catch errors at build time:\n\n## Converting to Compiled Bindings\n\nAdd `x:DataType` to your `ContentPage` element, pointing to your ViewModel:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout>\n        <Entry Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" />\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThat's the only XAML change needed — `x:DataType` tells the compiler the type of `BindingContext`, so all `{Binding}` expressions are validated at compile time.\n\n## Catching Binding Errors at Build Time\n\n**1. Enable strict mode in your `.csproj`:**\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <StrictXamlCompilation>true</StrictXamlCompilation>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**2. What this gives you:**\n\n- Misspelled property names (e.g., `{Binding Thme}`) → **compiler error**\n- Type mismatches (e.g., binding a `string` to `IsToggled`) → **compiler warning/error**\n- Missing properties on the declared DataType → **compiler error**\n\n**3. If you need to opt out locally** (e.g., for a dynamically-typed section):\n\n```xml\n<CollectionView x:DataType=\"{x:Null}\" ItemsSource=\"{Binding DynamicItems}\" />\n```\n\n## Summary\n\n| Step | What it does |\n|------|-------------|\n| Add `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` | Enables compiled bindings for the page |\n| Add `<StrictXamlCompilation>true</StrictXamlCompilation>` | Promotes binding issues to build errors |\n| Build normally (`dotnet build`) | Binding typos/mismatches now fail the build |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"79a8301f-8e71-4127-b5cc-b83677657bf1","outputTokens":579,"requestId":"142C:29F7F6:69DD410:722A890:6A03CBB9"},"id":"d34d88e5-3b40-4e06-a737-f42e1dfabea4","timestamp":"2026-05-13T00:54:29.030Z","parentId":"e23e80d8-4f00-4c22-901f-cd1bb931bacf"}
